<h1>Tic Tac Toe in Javascript!</h1>

<div id="board">
  <p id="result">Game in progress...</p>

  <div id="row-1" class="row">
    <span id="cell-1-1" class="cell"></span>
    <span id="cell-1-2" class="cell"></span>
    <span id="cell-1-3" class="cell"></span>
  </div>
  <div id="row-2" class="row">
    <span id="cell-2-1" class="cell"></span>
    <span id="cell-2-2" class="cell"></span>
    <span id="cell-2-3" class="cell"></span>
  </div>
  <div id="row-3" class="row">
    <span id="cell-3-1" class="cell"></span>
    <span id="cell-3-2" class="cell"></span>
    <span id="cell-3-3" class="cell"></span>
  </div>
</div>

<input type="checkbox" checked />When the user visits the site, they see an empty tic tac toe board.<br />
<input type="checkbox" checked />Moves are made by clicking in desired cell on the board.<br />
<input type="checkbox" checked />The user is always O, so they go first.<br />
<input type="checkbox" checked />The server plays as X. For the purpose of this prototype, the server plays the first available move, from left to right, top to bottom. This will make testing easy at the end.<br />
<input type="checkbox" checked />If the user clicks on an occupied cell, nothing should happen.<br />
<input type="checkbox" checked />The server must determine if the game is over, and report that to the client.<br />
<input type="checkbox" checked />After the first request (to load the html/css/js), requests should be async. (AJAX).<br />
